      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Enric (or Enrique) Monjo (1895-1976) was a Spanish sculptor.    Much of his work was religious in nature, including a number of pieces done for the National Cathedral in Washington, DC.   (See <extref href="http://dcmemorials.com/index_artist0000257.htm">dcmemorials.com/index_artist0000257.htm</extref> for a full listing.)</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Enric Monjo Papers</emph> consists of several exhibition catalogs in English, Spanish, and French, and photographs of Monjo's work.  The photographs are annotated on the back in Monjo's hand, with the title of the piece and the date(s) it was completed.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
